2. Tone Guidelines

General Tone: {{ Describe the “core personality” of the brand }}

Example: “Helpful expert friend,” “Bold strategist,” “Playful but smart,” etc.

Tone by Content Type

How-To / Educational Content
	•	Sounds like: {{ instructive, step-by-step, encouraging? }}
	•	Sample phrasing:
	•	“First, you’ll want to…”
	•	“Here’s how to think about this…”

Strategy / Thought Leadership
	•	Sounds like: {{ authoritative, insightful, experienced }}
	•	Sample phrasing:
	•	“Here’s what top performers do differently…”
	•	“The most effective approach is…”

Industry News / Trends
	•	Sounds like: {{ analytical, forward-looking }}
	•	Sample phrasing:
	•	“This shift means {{ audience }} should…”
	•	“Here’s why this matters…”

Product / Feature Content
	•	Sounds like: {{ benefit-focused, clear, transparent }}
	•	Sample phrasing:
	•	“This helps you {{ benefit }}…”
	•	“Here’s how it works…”

