5. Writing Style Guidelines

Sentence Structure
	•	Vary length (mix short + long)
	•	Prefer active voice
	•	Aim for clarity
	•	Keep the average sentence to {{ 15–20 words or brand preference }}

Paragraph Structure
	•	2–4 sentences each
	•	One idea per paragraph
	•	Use transitions to guide readers
	•	Add white space for readability

Word Choice
	•	Conversational ({{ define the tone })}
	•	Specific, not vague
	•	Action verbs: {{ add list that fits brand }}
	•	Avoid filler words unless intentional

Terminology

Say This → Not That
	•	{{ Preferred term }} → {{ Avoided term }}
	•	{{ Preferred term }} → {{ Avoided term }}
	•	{{ Preferred term }} → {{ Avoided term }}

⸻

6. Content Formatting Standards

Headlines
	•	Be specific
	•	Include benefits
	•	Prefer numbers when possible
	•	Keep concise ({{ 60 characters or client preference }})

Subheadings
	•	Descriptive
	•	Keyword-rich
	•	Parallel structure
	•	Scannable

Lists
	•	Numbered for steps
	•	Bulleted for ideas
	•	Keep formatting parallel
	•	Make information skimmable

Calls-to-Action
	•	Clear action (“{{ CTA example }}”)
	•	Value-focused
	•	Match funnel stage
	•	Natural placement

